      "On the other hand, a sinus lift method, also known as sinus elevation, enhances the amount of bone in the upper jaw by ‘lifting’ the sinus membrane up and putting in graft material beneath it. It’s a common preparatory step for individuals who need dental implants but lack enough natural jawbone.",
