      "Sinus lift procedures involve adding bone between the upper jaw and maxillary sinuses on either side of the nose. An incision is made where the back teeth used to be. The tissue is raised to access the sinus, and the grafting material is placed. The amount of extra height depends on individual needs for dental implants.",
